commit.message:
Don’t import from collections generally, but directly from collections.abc.

Fixes #5
Clean up poorly build py2k/py3k compatbility.

MANIFEST.in: add LICENSE

Signed-off-by: Asaf Kahlon <asafka7@gmail.com>

Fixed iteritems/itervalues for SortedDicts in Python 2.7

sortedcontainers v2.0.4 removed iteritems/itervalues on SortedDicts (they now
raise an AttributeError exception), which breaks the _SortedNode class.

Check if the object has an iteritems/itervalues attribute before calling it.
Added README, updated setup.py & gitignore and bumped to 0.3
Add pylintrc and disable some pylint warnings
Fix longest_prefix* and iter_prefix* methods to work for empty string (or zero length in general) keys
Add an optimized __bool__/__nonzero__ method instead of falling back to slower __len__
Add sortedcontainers dependency and drop quick and dirty _SortedDict
Define a __cmp__ method for Trie (fixes intermittent test failures)
Change hgignore to gitignore and update it
Fixed longest_prefix_*  in cases there are longer prefixes that partially match

- Renamed trie module to pytrie.
- Added documentation
- Trie:
    - Removed iterprefixeditems, __copy__
    - Added longest_prefix, longest_prefix_value, longest_prefix_item
    - Added iter_prefixes, iter_prefix_values, iter_prefix_items
    - Added __repr__
- Added StringTrie, SortedTrie, SortedStringTrie
- Node:
    - Removed size, __eq__
    - Added numkeys
